Which clusters belong to which germ layers?

library(Seurat)
library(tidyverse)
library(RColorBrewer)

Load umap whole.

load("/Volumes/Bud_SSD/20210505-seurat/flox-integr-clust-5/umap-by-cluster-flox-integr-clust-5-18.Robj")
head(whole.umap)
table(whole.umap$wildtype.whole)

Set germ layers.

whole.umap$germ.whole <- recode(whole.umap$wildtype.whole, 
                                "W1.1.1" = "ECT", 
                                "W1.1.2" = "ECT", 
                                "W1.1.3" = "ECT", 
                                "W1.2" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.1.1" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.1.2" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.1.3" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.2.1" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.2.2" = "MES", 
                                "W2.1.2.3" = "MES", 
                                "W2.2.1" = "MES",  
                                "W2.2.2" = "MES",  
                                "W3.1" = "END", 
                                "W3.2" = "END", 
                                "W3.3" = "ECT", 
                                "W4.1" = "MES", 
                                "W4.2" = "MES", 
                                "W5" = "MES")

whole.umap$germ.whole <- factor(whole.umap$germ.whole, levels = c("ECT", "MES", "END"))
save(whole.umap, file = "/Volumes/Bud_SSD/20210505-seurat/flox-integr-clust-5/umap-by-germ-layer-flox-integr-clust-5-18.Robj")

Generate label umap.

whole.label <- whole.umap %>% group_by(germ.whole) %>% summarize(umap.1 = median(umap.1), umap.2 = median(umap.2))

Generate cluster umap.

cluster.umap <- ggplot() +
geom_point(data = sample(whole.umap), mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, color = germ.whole), size = 0.1) +
geom_text(data = whole.label, mapping = aes(x = umap.1, y = umap.2, label = germ.whole), size = 3.5) +
labs(title = "Whole, Nipbl Flox/+", x = "UMAP 1", y = "UMAP 2", color = "Germ\nLayer") +
guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 2.3))) +
theme_classic(base_size = 7) +
theme(axis.line = element_blank(), axis.ticks = element_blank(), axis.text = element_blank(), plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 7), legend.key.size = unit(7, "pt"))

cluster.umap

ggsave(plot = cluster.umap, filename = "/Volumes/Bud_SSD/20210505-seurat/flox-integr-clust-5/umap-by-germ-layer-flox-integr-clust-5-18.png", device = "png", width = 6.5, height = 4.5, units = "in")
